title: What are the personalities of the Stray Kids members? - Quora

response.answer_text: let’s get iiiit chan: very humble, extremely caring. he loves the members a lot and isn’t afraid to show it at all. he’s also very passionate about music (writing and producing). woojin: one word; soft. he’s very goofy and calm. in interviews, he mostly listens to what the other members say, and doesn’t talk much. he’s the oldest member, so he, like chan, cares for the younger ones a lot. changbin: at first, he seems very dark. when i first got into skz, he scared me. but he really i just another soft crackhead of the group. he also spits fire. he, like chan, is also very passionate about producing and writing lyrics. minho: he, much like changbin, seems very dark. he’s pretty shy, meaning he doesn’t talk much in interviews. but, he’s amazing at dancing and is very charismatic on stage. (one of the reasons why he’s my bias.) hyunjin: he’s very dramatic. in a good way. when he’s with other people (not the members) he seems pretty uncomfortable/shy. but he’s the definition of a crackhead. like minho, he’s part of the dance line, so he’s very passionate about dancing. jisung: jokes. a lot of them. he gets called squirrel by the members, due to him stuffing his cheeks with food. he’s amazing at rapping, and is part of 3racha along with chan and changbin. he’s also very soft. <3 felix: he’s pretty serious. like when they do dance practices, the other members fool around, while he’s completely focused on dancing. in their vlives though, he’s very chaotic. he’s also part of the dance line, with minho and hyunjin. seungmin: he seems scary at first, but he’s actually just a soft baby boy. he resembles a puppy a lot, due to his big eyes. he’s one of the (if not the) cutest members of the group. i personally think his dancing skills are underrated. jeongin: baby boy culture once again. he’s also very cute. i don’t have much to write about him, but he’s very kindhearted and loves all of his hyungs. i am aware that i put minho and changbin in the wrong order but i’m too lazy to change it. ~aria louise
